The sea has a current.

256
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:46,426
It'll push us past the island
and pull us out to sea,

257
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:48,011
and we'll drown.

258
00:14:48,178 --> 00:14:50,597
HOLMES: Don't, don't, don't,

259
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:52,849
don't look
at what's in front of you...

260
00:14:53,016 --> 00:14:56,478
Boots, boots, boots, boots,

261
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:58,105
moving up and down again

262
00:14:58,272 --> 00:15:01,316
Men, men, men, men,

263
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:03,193
men go mad with watchin' em...

264
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,237
We'll have four hours
before high tide.

265
00:15:06,947 --> 00:15:07,948
Are we doing this?

266
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:10,534
Can't go back now, Dad.

267
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:11,702
Why?

268
00:15:12,327 --> 00:15:13,453
Everyone'll think I'm soft.

269
00:15:13,537 --> 00:15:14,705
[CHUCKLES]

270
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:15,789
Aye, they will.

271
00:15:15,956 --> 00:15:17,916
Can't have that, can we?
[CHUCKLES]

272
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,418
Come on, then. [LAUGHS]

273
00:15:19,501 --> 00:15:22,129
HOLMES: Count, count, count,

274
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:24,423
count the bullets
in the bandoliers.

275
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:27,759
If your eyes drop,

276
00:15:27,926 --> 00:15:29,261
they will get atop of you!

277
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:32,681
Boots, boots, boots, boots,

278
00:15:32,848 --> 00:15:34,558
moving up and down again

279
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:37,561
There's no discharge
in the war!

280
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:39,771
JAMIE: This is where
we get all the fuel.

281
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:42,816
You'll be working here
one day.

282
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:46,361
HOLMES: Ain't so bad by day

283
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:47,613
because o' company,

284
00:15:47,696 --> 00:15:50,574
But night brings long

285
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:52,409
strings
o' forty thousand million

286
00:15:52,492 --> 00:15:55,579
Boots, boots, boots, boots,

287
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:57,289
moving up and down again.

288
00:15:57,372 --> 00:15:58,498
SPIKE: It's so big.

289
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:01,084
-[SIGHS]
-If we kept walking,

290
00:16:01,251 --> 00:16:03,420
would we get to a place
where you can't see the sea?

291
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,589
[CHUCKLES] Wey aye.

292
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:08,050
You'll walk for days or weeks
without seeing the coast.

293
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:10,260
There's nothing out there,
Spikey.

294
00:16:10,886 --> 00:16:12,512
Nowhere to aim for.

295
00:16:12,721 --> 00:16:13,931
There's other villages.

296
00:16:14,181 --> 00:16:16,225
Aye, but none have
anything we don't have.

297
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:18,018
And we stay out
the towns and villages.

298
00:16:18,101 --> 00:16:20,270
HOLMES: I have marched

299
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:21,647
-six weeks...
-JAMIE: Howay.

300
00:16:21,730 --> 00:16:23,106
HOLMES: ...in hell an' certify

301
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:25,651
It is not fire,

302
00:16:25,734 --> 00:16:27,486
devils, dark, or anything,

303
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:30,948
but boots, boots,
boots, boots,

304
00:16:31,031 --> 00:16:32,699
moving up an' down again.

305
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:36,328
[SOFT SNARLING AND GRUNTING]

306
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:41,333
-Try, try, try...
-[SNARLING]

307
00:16:41,416 --> 00:16:43,961
...try to think
of something different

308
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:46,171
Oh, my God,

309
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,715
keep me from going lunatic!

310
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:52,177
Boots, boots, boots, boots,

311
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,096
moving up and down again!

312
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:57,474
There's no discharge
in the war!

313
00:17:05,357 --> 00:17:06,608
[SOFT MOANING]

314
00:17:11,946 --> 00:17:13,949
There, look, look, look,
look, look, look.

315
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:16,952
Slow-low.

316
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:19,663
Not fast.

317
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:22,541
Doesn't mean
they aren't dangerous.

318
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,627
And if there's one visible,

319
00:17:26,168 --> 00:17:28,213
probably a couple more
in the trees.

320
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:32,676
Your bow

321
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:34,928
isn't strong enough
for the chest.

322
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:37,681
You need to hit it
right in the neck.

323
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:40,434
Okay, Dad.

324
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:46,440
JAMIE: You scared?

325
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:48,734
Only a little bit.

326
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:52,529
Are you?

327
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:53,614
No. I'm good.

328
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:58,285
You like this range?

329
00:17:58,744 --> 00:17:59,870
SPIKE: I think so.

330
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:01,538
Let's go get your first kill.

331
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:18,472
[SLURPING AND COOING]

332
00:18:20,515 --> 00:18:21,683
Get him in your sight.

333
00:18:29,983 --> 00:18:31,193
Calculate for wind.

334
00:18:33,695 --> 00:18:34,696
All right.

335
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:36,365
He's yours.

336
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:39,409
Anything that comes out
after him is mine.

337
00:18:39,743 --> 00:18:40,869
Send when ready.

338
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:44,623
[SCREECHES]

339
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:45,916
Send it.

340
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:48,961
[SQUEALING]

341
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,929
[CHOKING, WHEEZING]

342
00:18:59,012 --> 00:19:00,514
[WHINING]

343
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:07,896
[SHRIEKS]

344
00:19:11,191 --> 00:19:12,818
[SHRIEKS]

345
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:18,323
[WHIMPERING]

346
00:19:21,159 --> 00:19:22,160
SPIKE: Dad!

347
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:27,583
BOY 1: Get in here!
BOY 2: Hey!

348
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:32,588
Beautiful kill, Spike.

349
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:34,131
You feel good?

350
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:35,632
Yeah, I think so.

351
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:36,717
JAMIE: Aye, you should.

352
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:38,886
I'm proud of ya.

353
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:41,096
Now come on, we gotta move.

354
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:42,848
The screaming
would have alerted

355
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:44,224
the other infected
in the area.

356
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:47,561
Go on. Let's keep going.
[LAUGHS]

357
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:53,317
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

358
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:14,213
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

359
00:20:26,516 --> 00:20:28,477
[FOOTFALLS RUMBLING]

360
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:42,574
They're amazing.

361
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:44,868
JAMIE: They're beautiful.

362
00:20:49,831 --> 00:20:50,832
Here.

363
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,293
Check this out.

364
00:21:00,884 --> 00:21:01,885
Good lad.

365
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,434
[LIQUID DRIPPING]

366
00:21:16,858 --> 00:21:18,402
[DOOR CREAKS]

367
00:21:24,324 --> 00:21:26,326
-[FOX YELPS]
-Shit.

368
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,869
[SPIKE PANTING]

369
00:21:33,584 --> 00:21:35,335
It's always worth looking
around for summat useful.

370
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:39,673
People would have searched
this place a hundred times,

371
00:21:39,756 --> 00:21:40,757
but you never know.

372
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:46,638
[PIANO KEYS RATTLE]

373
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:52,811
Fuckin' hell.

374
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:58,442
[CHUCKLING] Oh.

375
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:01,904
SPIKE: Are these useful?

376
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:04,656
Nah. Got plenty of that.

377
00:22:04,823 --> 00:22:05,824
But this is.

378
00:22:07,034 --> 00:22:08,035
What is it?

379
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:10,412
A frisbee.

380
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:12,164
You never seen
a frisbee before?

381
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:14,333
Aw, it's great.

382
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,126
You're gonna love it.

383
00:22:16,210 --> 00:22:17,961
-[HIGH-PITCHED CRY]
-[GASPING]

384
00:22:19,713 --> 00:22:20,797
[CAWING]

385
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:24,468
[CAWING]

386
00:22:27,638 --> 00:22:28,722
[CAWING]

387
00:22:32,935 --> 00:22:34,561
[CROW CRIES]

388
00:22:37,648 --> 00:22:39,233
[LIQUID DRIPPING]

389
00:22:43,528 --> 00:22:44,696
Come here, son.

390
00:22:48,283 --> 00:22:49,451
[GASPS]

391
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:57,292
Don't look away, Spike.

392
00:22:58,126 --> 00:22:59,294
-Dad, please.
-Spike!

393
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:00,754
Do as I tell ya.

394
00:23:04,883 --> 00:23:06,343
There's a lesson for you here.

395
00:23:09,763 --> 00:23:10,973
[COUGHS]

396
00:23:17,604 --> 00:23:19,064
[MUFFLED SCREAM]

397
00:23:19,147 --> 00:23:21,441
[MUFFLED GROWLING]

398
00:23:26,196 --> 00:23:27,322
What happened to him?

399
00:23:28,865 --> 00:23:31,326
Looks like he got tied up
and left for the infected.

400
00:23:32,578 --> 00:23:33,870
And now he's infected.

401
00:23:34,663 --> 00:23:35,706
He's infected?

402
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:38,333
[MUFFLED SNARLING]

403
00:23:39,877 --> 00:23:40,878
JAMIE: Aye.

404
00:23:41,336 --> 00:23:42,713
Why would anyone do that?

405
00:23:43,589 --> 00:23:44,756
JAMIE: Maybe a punishment.

406
00:23:47,843 --> 00:23:48,844
Maybe a warning.

407
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,557
There are strange people
on the mainland.

408
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:56,059
Roaming.

409
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:58,937
That's why our home
is so precious.

410
00:24:02,024 --> 00:24:03,317
Is that the lesson?

411
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:04,776
No.

412
00:24:06,361 --> 00:24:08,405
-Kill it.
-[SNARLING CONTINUES]

413
00:24:10,824 --> 00:24:13,076
The more you kill,
the easier it gets.

414
00:24:14,369 --> 00:24:15,370
[SIGHS]

415
00:24:16,622 --> 00:24:18,123
Don't feel bad about it.

416
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:20,334
The infection
takes away their minds.

417
00:24:21,043 --> 00:24:22,085
[SNARLS]

418
00:24:22,169 --> 00:24:24,004
It's got no mind,
it's got no soul.

419
00:24:33,138 --> 00:24:34,056
Spike.

420
00:24:35,599 --> 00:24:36,683
Kill the bloody thing.

421
00:24:38,393 --> 00:24:39,311
Kill it!

422
00:24:40,646 --> 00:24:42,522
What are you waiting for,
Spike?

423
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:44,316
Now, son!

424
00:24:45,359 --> 00:24:46,276
Spike, finish it!

425
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:49,780
For Christ's sake, Spike,
fuckin' kill it!

426
00:24:55,786 --> 00:24:57,496
[GASPING]

427
00:24:59,206 --> 00:25:00,207
Good lad.

428
00:25:05,963 --> 00:25:07,965
[HYMNAL MUSIC PLAYING]

429
00:25:14,972 --> 00:25:18,183
[SINGING] Abide with me

430
00:25:18,809 --> 00:25:24,314
Fast falls the eventide

431
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:29,778
The darkness deepens

432
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:34,199
Lord, with me abide

433
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:38,620
Where is death's sting?

434
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:43,041
-Head. Heart. Draw...
-Where, grave, thy victory?

435
00:25:45,252 --> 00:25:46,837
I triumph still

436
00:25:47,004 --> 00:25:48,005
Release.

437
00:25:49,631 --> 00:25:51,425
If Thou abide...

438
00:25:54,469 --> 00:25:56,430
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

439
00:26:08,191 --> 00:26:09,526
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

440
00:26:09,610 --> 00:26:11,445
[FLIES BUZZING]

441
00:26:21,788 --> 00:26:23,665
JAMIE: There's another kill
here if we're lucky.

442
00:26:24,499 --> 00:26:25,542
Come on.

443
00:26:28,045 --> 00:26:29,087
JAMIE: Oh.

444
00:26:37,846 --> 00:26:39,097
This wasn't slow-lows.

445
00:26:40,515 --> 00:26:42,100
This were
the fast ones, Spikey.

446
00:26:44,811 --> 00:26:45,812
[GAGS]

447
00:26:46,688 --> 00:26:48,357
You smell that? [LAUGHS]

448
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,441
It's the intestines.

449
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:53,570
I weirdly like it. [ECHOING]

450
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:05,040
[FLIES BUZZING]

451
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:08,669
Dad. [BREATHING HEAVILY]

452
00:27:09,628 --> 00:27:10,796
Dad.

453
00:27:20,347 --> 00:27:21,640
[GRUNTS]

454
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:26,019
-[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]
-[PANTING AND SNARLING]

455
00:27:28,272 --> 00:27:29,898
[LOW GROWLING]

456
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:38,782
What?

457
00:27:40,993 --> 00:27:42,828
An Alpha did that.
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

458
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:46,915
This way, Spike. Come on.

459
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:48,166
Spike! Move it!

460
00:27:51,461 --> 00:27:52,504
We're going back?

461
00:27:53,839 --> 00:27:56,216
Aye. Got your kills,
that's what we came for.

462
00:27:57,926 --> 00:27:59,011
Won't it look like
we left early?

463
00:27:59,094 --> 00:28:01,722
Don't talk, Spikey.
Just keep your eyes peeled.

464
00:28:01,805 --> 00:28:02,931
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

465
00:28:03,015 --> 00:28:04,349
[PANTING]

466
00:28:06,184 --> 00:28:07,144
Looks clear.

467
00:28:07,811 --> 00:28:08,812
Let's go.

468
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:15,944
-[SOFT GROWL]
-[JAMIE SHUSHING]

469
00:28:16,028 --> 00:28:17,029
[DISTANT CRY]

470
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:26,496
Stay really still.

471
00:28:27,581 --> 00:28:29,708
[DISTANT YELLING AND GROWLING]

472
00:28:34,922 --> 00:28:36,632
[SNARLING]

473
00:28:41,011 --> 00:28:43,263
[GRUNTING AND HOOTING]

474
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:48,185
JAMIE: Alpha.

475
00:28:48,977 --> 00:28:49,978
Fuck.

476
00:28:50,604 --> 00:28:51,855
Get back to the trees.

477
00:28:51,939 --> 00:28:53,315
Get back, let's go.

478
00:28:53,774 --> 00:28:54,775
Dad!

479
00:28:55,609 --> 00:28:57,194
[ALPHA ROARS]

480
00:28:57,277 --> 00:28:59,905
[INFECTED SHRIEKING
AND SNARLING]

481
00:29:09,539 --> 00:29:10,791
Let's go!

482
00:29:12,251 --> 00:29:14,253
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

483
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:17,714
Move, move.

484
00:29:18,507 --> 00:29:20,300
Keep moving.
Let's go, let's go!

485
00:29:23,053 --> 00:29:25,013
Here, defence.
Get your breath back.

486
00:29:25,681 --> 00:29:26,765
I'll take the first,

487
00:29:26,848 --> 00:29:28,183
-you take the second.
-Yeah.

488
00:29:29,268 --> 00:29:30,227
Slow your breathing.

489
00:29:30,978 --> 00:29:31,979
Slow it down.

490
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:34,773
[YELPS]

491
00:29:34,856 --> 00:29:35,941
Shit!

492
00:29:36,191 --> 00:29:37,818
[SPIKE HYPERVENTILATING]

493
00:29:42,823 --> 00:29:44,992
Go! Move, move, move!

494
00:29:45,158 --> 00:29:46,243
Just go!

495
00:29:47,619 --> 00:29:48,620
Fuck!

496
00:29:51,039 --> 00:29:53,500
Right, two-man drill. Defence!

497
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:01,508
Right. Shoot!

498
00:30:02,551 --> 00:30:05,470
Head and heart.
Head and heart, Spike.

499
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:15,814
Get in there.

500
00:30:17,274 --> 00:30:18,275
Go up!

501
00:30:22,946 --> 00:30:24,031
[GROWLING]

502
00:30:24,781 --> 00:30:25,782
-Go on, son!
-SPIKE: Come on, Dad!

503
00:30:25,866 --> 00:30:26,867
Where?

504
00:30:29,244 --> 00:30:30,287
Shit.

505
00:30:32,289 --> 00:30:33,415
Da, what...?

506
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:34,499
JAMIE: The loft!
Check the loft!

507
00:30:38,337 --> 00:30:40,172
Oi. Come here.

508
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:45,677
Go on.

509
00:30:45,844 --> 00:30:47,012
SPIKE: I can't get back up.

510
00:30:47,179 --> 00:30:49,389
-Oh, fuck.
-Dad! Dad!

511
00:30:57,648 --> 00:30:58,899
JAMIE: Push!

512
00:31:03,946 --> 00:31:04,947
JAMIE: Oh, fuck.

513
00:31:07,074 --> 00:31:08,742
[INFECTED SHRIEKING]

514
00:31:12,746 --> 00:31:13,747
Fuckin' hell.

515
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:18,877
[JAMIE CHUCKLES]

516
00:31:22,339 --> 00:31:24,174
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

517
00:31:55,789 --> 00:31:57,249
SAM: Mind your backs, boys.

518
00:31:57,916 --> 00:31:59,042
Coming through!

519
00:32:00,085 --> 00:32:01,420
Tea time.

520
00:32:02,296 --> 00:32:03,839
Tea time. Well done today.

521
00:32:04,506 --> 00:32:05,674
Great stuff.

522
00:32:06,717 --> 00:32:08,468
Chop chop before it gets dark.

523
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:26,403
JAMIE: It's waitin'.

524
00:32:28,030 --> 00:32:29,740
Alphas aren't like the others.

525
00:32:30,407 --> 00:32:33,201
Not just bigger. Smarter.

526
00:32:33,994 --> 00:32:35,203
SPIKE: What are we gonna do?

527
00:32:36,121 --> 00:32:37,456
Well, we're not fighting it.

528
00:32:39,917 --> 00:32:41,376
I've got no arrows left.

529
00:32:43,462 --> 00:32:44,463
And anyway...

530
00:32:44,630 --> 00:32:47,674
I've seen it take a dozen hits
to drop one of those things.

531
00:32:49,051 --> 00:32:51,303
So, we'll wait, too.

532
00:32:54,348 --> 00:32:56,016
I'm really sorry, Dad.

533
00:32:56,642 --> 00:32:58,185
What? What about?

534
00:32:59,311 --> 00:33:00,896
This is all my fault.

535
00:33:01,396 --> 00:33:03,398
-I couldn't hit anything.
-What are you talking about?

536
00:33:03,482 --> 00:33:06,318
I tried but I was too scared.
And I kept missing.

537
00:33:06,401 --> 00:33:08,362
What are you talking about?
This is not your fault.

538
00:33:08,528 --> 00:33:09,988
And you kept shooting.

539
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:12,449
I've seen adults who canna get
an arrow in the bow,

540
00:33:12,532 --> 00:33:13,742
they're shaking so hard.

541
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:15,994
Not you. Hey, hey, hey...

542
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:19,081
Spike, you did well.

543
00:33:20,791 --> 00:33:21,875
Honestly.

544
00:33:27,548 --> 00:33:28,966
SPIKE: We're gonna miss
the low tide.

545
00:33:29,591 --> 00:33:31,009
JAMIE: Yeah. Yeah.
SPIKE: Aren't we?

546
00:33:31,176 --> 00:33:32,386
There'll be another.

547
00:33:43,772 --> 00:33:45,566
Hey, look out to sea.

548
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:48,151
Here.

549
00:33:51,572 --> 00:33:52,573
Just there.

550
00:33:53,949 --> 00:33:55,534
Quarantine patrol.

551
00:33:56,702 --> 00:33:57,869
Probably French.

552
00:34:02,374 --> 00:34:04,376
[DISTANT CRIES]

553
00:34:17,264 --> 00:34:18,265
Dad...

554
00:34:19,558 --> 00:34:20,558
What's that?

555
00:34:27,149 --> 00:34:29,275
[SIGHS] Fire.

556
00:34:29,692 --> 00:34:31,236
Something's burning?

557
00:34:32,154 --> 00:34:33,154
JAMIE: Yeah.

558
00:34:33,947 --> 00:34:34,948
Something.

559
00:34:36,617 --> 00:34:37,826
Is it another village?

560
00:34:39,536 --> 00:34:40,536
Nope.

561
00:34:42,331 --> 00:34:43,332
What is it then?

562
00:34:44,082 --> 00:34:46,210
I don't know.
I've never been there.

563
00:34:47,835 --> 00:34:48,837
SPIKE: Does it always burn?

564
00:34:49,004 --> 00:34:50,839
I just said
I've never been there, Spike.

565
00:35:10,150 --> 00:35:11,485
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

566
00:35:12,194 --> 00:35:14,279
[SERENE CLASSICAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

567
00:35:16,323 --> 00:35:17,741
[GAGGING AND GRUNTING]

568
00:35:23,413 --> 00:35:24,581
Spike.

569
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:28,168
Spike.

570
00:35:28,544 --> 00:35:29,545
There she is.

571
00:35:29,753 --> 00:35:31,129
Spike, I'm drowning.

572
00:35:31,213 --> 00:35:33,507
[RUMBLING]

573
00:35:43,100 --> 00:35:45,394
[SERENE CLASSICAL
MUSIC CONTINUES]

574
00:35:53,735 --> 00:35:55,279
Get out! We gotta get out!

575
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,281
Oh, fucking hell.

576
00:35:58,574 --> 00:35:59,992
Get up! Get up, Spike!

577
00:36:01,118 --> 00:36:03,120
-Get your bum down.
-Wake up, we've gotta move!

578
00:36:03,203 --> 00:36:05,163
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

579
00:36:09,751 --> 00:36:11,336
It's all right, son.
It's all right.

580
00:36:11,962 --> 00:36:13,422
Aah! Fuckin' hell!

581
00:36:17,259 --> 00:36:19,136
[SPIKE COUGHING]

582
00:36:19,219 --> 00:36:20,262
What happened?

583
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:21,388
Old building.

584
00:36:22,222 --> 00:36:24,683
I dunno.
Chimney fuckin' died on us.

585
00:36:25,058 --> 00:36:26,268
The noise will bring 'em.

586
00:36:26,351 --> 00:36:27,561
We gotta move.

587
00:36:28,437 --> 00:36:30,272
SPIKE: Is it low tide?
JAMIE: It'll be low enough.

588
00:36:31,815 --> 00:36:33,358
We move fast but quiet.

589
00:36:33,525 --> 00:36:35,527
If you see the Alpha,
just run straight

590
00:36:35,611 --> 00:36:37,905
for the causeway
and over it. All right?

591
00:36:37,988 --> 00:36:40,157
You stop for nothing! Go on!

592
00:36:40,449 --> 00:36:42,367
-Where will you be?
-Right behind you.

593
00:36:45,329 --> 00:36:48,874
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

594
00:36:54,213 --> 00:36:56,757
-[MUSIC STOPS]
-[PANTING]

595
00:36:59,718 --> 00:37:01,094
JAMIE: No sign of the Alpha.

596
00:37:02,221 --> 00:37:03,430
SPIKE: It's still high tide.

597
00:37:03,597 --> 00:37:04,765
JAMIE: Only just.

598
00:37:04,932 --> 00:37:06,725
The water will be shallow.
But we can make it.

599
00:37:19,196 --> 00:37:21,323
Shin-deep.
We're good. All right.

600
00:37:22,282 --> 00:37:23,408
Take your boots off.

601
00:37:24,284 --> 00:37:26,328
Aye. Line up the gates.

602
00:37:27,663 --> 00:37:28,664
That's our path.

603
00:37:29,331 --> 00:37:32,000
-[BREATHING HEAVILY]
-It's okay. Just breathe.

604
00:37:32,292 --> 00:37:33,835
Here. Let's go.

605
00:37:34,878 --> 00:37:35,879
You go first.

606
00:37:39,424 --> 00:37:41,093
[SERENE CLASSICAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

607
00:37:41,176 --> 00:37:42,219
Go on, son.

608
00:37:44,805 --> 00:37:46,431
[PANTING]

609
00:37:47,266 --> 00:37:48,850
[BIRDS CHITTERING]

610
00:37:51,311 --> 00:37:52,563
[GROWLS SOFTLY]

611
00:38:01,989 --> 00:38:03,365
[CHUCKLING]

612
00:38:03,907 --> 00:38:07,119
How about that day, Spike, eh?

613
00:38:07,536 --> 00:38:09,204
First time to the mainland.

614
00:38:09,288 --> 00:38:11,999
First kill. First run-in
with the infected.

615
00:38:12,082 --> 00:38:13,250
[PANTING]

616
00:38:13,333 --> 00:38:15,544
Saw an Alpha! [CHUCKLES]

617
00:38:15,627 --> 00:38:16,670
And missed the tide.

618
00:38:17,838 --> 00:38:19,715
SPIKE: I've got so much
to tell Mum when we get back.

619
00:38:19,798 --> 00:38:21,592
[JAMIE WHOOPING, ECHOES]

620
00:38:23,635 --> 00:38:25,137
[WHOOSHING]

621
00:38:32,853 --> 00:38:34,605
[SERENE CLASSICAL
MUSIC CONTINUES]

622
00:38:34,688 --> 00:38:36,815
-[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
-[DISTANT PANTING]

623
00:38:38,734 --> 00:38:39,735
SPIKE: Dad.

624
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,654
Run, Spike!

625
00:38:44,031 --> 00:38:44,990
Run!

626
00:38:46,241 --> 00:38:48,327
-[SPIKE SHOUTING IN PANIC]
-Go! Go, keep going!

627
00:38:54,958 --> 00:38:55,959
Keep moving!

628
00:38:58,003 --> 00:39:00,172
-Oh! Oh, God! Get up!
-Dad, I can't!

629
00:39:00,255 --> 00:39:02,716
-I can't!
-Spike! Get up, now!

630
00:39:04,301 --> 00:39:06,511
Spike, go! Go, go, Spike!

631
00:39:07,429 --> 00:39:08,430
Fucking go!

632
00:39:08,513 --> 00:39:10,307
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

633
00:39:13,810 --> 00:39:14,770
SPIKE: I can't!

634
00:39:14,853 --> 00:39:15,979
JAMIE: Yes, you can!

635
00:39:21,026 --> 00:39:22,027
Oh, shit!

636
00:39:22,653 --> 00:39:24,404
[ALPHA GROWLS]

637
00:39:25,614 --> 00:39:27,491
JAMIE: [DISTANTLY] Incoming!

638
00:39:28,242 --> 00:39:29,493
Open up!

639
00:39:29,576 --> 00:39:31,578
[SERENE CLASSICAL
MUSIC RESUMES]

640
00:39:31,662 --> 00:39:35,457
-[WHISTLE BLOWING]
-Help! Jenny! Jenny!

641
00:39:36,500 --> 00:39:38,627
ANTHONY: Wakey, wakey!
Up, up, up!

642
00:39:38,794 --> 00:39:39,878
Incoming!

643
00:39:40,045 --> 00:39:41,505
Incoming!

644
00:39:42,422 --> 00:39:43,423
-Wakey, wakey, boys.
-JENNY: Ant, who is it?

645
00:39:43,507 --> 00:39:45,217
-Everyone up! Eyes on!
-Form up, boys! Get ready!

646
00:39:45,300 --> 00:39:47,344
ANTHONY: Eyes on, eyes on!
JAMIE: Incoming!

647
00:39:48,387 --> 00:39:49,471
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

648
00:39:53,767 --> 00:39:55,143
Alpha!

649
00:39:55,602 --> 00:39:58,105
Open up! Fucking open up!

650
00:39:59,064 --> 00:40:00,607
Alpha! Alpha!

651
00:40:00,816 --> 00:40:02,401
ANTHONY: Fuckin' Alpha,
get that light on!

652
00:40:02,484 --> 00:40:03,485
Keep the fuckin' light on him!

653
00:40:03,569 --> 00:40:05,654
JENNY: Fire!
JAMIE: Get down!

654
00:40:06,405 --> 00:40:08,031
[GROWLING]

655
00:40:12,578 --> 00:40:13,662
[ROARS]

656
00:40:13,745 --> 00:40:16,832
JAMIE: Go, go, go, go, Spike!
Go, go.

657
00:40:16,915 --> 00:40:18,125
ANTHONY: Keep
that fuckin' light on him.

658
00:40:18,208 --> 00:40:20,752
Load it, load it, load it!

659
00:40:20,836 --> 00:40:23,005
JAMIE: Oh, fuck.
This is it, Spike.

660
00:40:23,714 --> 00:40:24,840
Breathe!

661
00:40:27,134 --> 00:40:28,135
[GROANS]

662
00:40:29,511 --> 00:40:31,096
Shit! Oh!

663
00:40:33,098 --> 00:40:35,851
[SINGING] Oh me lads,
you should've seen us gannin'

664
00:40:35,934 --> 00:40:36,977
Passing the folks
along the road

665
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:38,061
Open up!

666
00:40:38,145 --> 00:40:40,022
Just as they were stannin'
All the lads and lasses

667
00:40:40,105 --> 00:40:42,691
-There all wi' smilin' faces
-Jenny! Open the fucking gate!

668
00:40:42,774 --> 00:40:43,859
-Gannin' along
-Wait.

669
00:40:43,942 --> 00:40:44,943
The Scotswood Road

670
00:40:45,027 --> 00:40:46,820
JAMIE: No, fucking open up!

671
00:40:48,363 --> 00:40:49,323
Fuck's sake!

672
00:40:49,406 --> 00:40:50,365
-Wait.
-No.

673
00:40:50,449 --> 00:40:52,034
-Fuckin' hell, Jenny!
-SPIKE: Please, please.

674
00:40:52,117 --> 00:40:53,201
-JAMIE: We're fuckin' good.
-Wait.

675
00:40:53,994 --> 00:40:55,287
Look at me fuckin' eyes,

676
00:40:55,370 --> 00:40:56,788
-we're clean.
-Wait.

677
00:40:56,872 --> 00:40:59,291
[VOCALISING]

678
00:40:59,541 --> 00:41:00,667
Look at him.

679
00:41:00,751 --> 00:41:01,877
-Look at his eyes!
-Jenny.

680
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:04,171
-He's clean! We're clean!
-Jenny, please.

681
00:41:05,130 --> 00:41:06,506
All right, open up,
let them in.

682
00:41:06,590 --> 00:41:07,883
Go. Go.

683
00:41:08,175 --> 00:41:11,303
To see the Blaydon Races

684
00:41:11,386 --> 00:41:13,013
-[SONG ENDS]
-[ALL CHEER]

685
00:41:17,017 --> 00:41:18,268
CROWD: [CHANTING]
Spike! Spike!

686
00:41:18,435 --> 00:41:21,939
Spike! Spike! Spike!
Spike! Spike! Spike!

687
00:41:22,564 --> 00:41:23,857
Hey!

688
00:41:24,024 --> 00:41:26,735
There were 25, 'bout 30 yards.

689
00:41:26,902 --> 00:41:29,154
Tall grass. Wind.

690
00:41:29,238 --> 00:41:30,489
[CROWD EXCLAIMS]

691
00:41:30,572 --> 00:41:32,241
And where does that arrow go?

692
00:41:33,283 --> 00:41:35,327
Right through
his fuckin' neck!

693
00:41:35,410 --> 00:41:36,954
[ALL CHEERING]

694
00:41:39,748 --> 00:41:41,833
That fat bastard, he stands up

695
00:41:41,917 --> 00:41:43,794
and lets out one
of them girly screams...

696
00:41:43,877 --> 00:41:45,546
[IMITATES SLOW-LOW'S SCREAM]

697
00:41:45,629 --> 00:41:48,423
and then drops
like a sack of fuckin' shite.

698
00:41:48,507 --> 00:41:49,967
[CHEERING AND LAUGHING]

699
00:41:51,176 --> 00:41:54,054
Next thing, we've got
eight fuckin' infected...

700
00:41:54,137 --> 00:41:55,556
Dad, swearing.

701
00:41:55,722 --> 00:41:57,349
...running right at us!

702
00:41:57,432 --> 00:41:58,725
[CHEERING]

703
00:41:59,977 --> 00:42:02,354
I'm thinking,
"Oh, shit, here we go."

704
00:42:03,146 --> 00:42:06,525
Benny Big Bollocks here
is just fuckin' taking shots.

705
00:42:06,608 --> 00:42:07,943
[LAUGHING]

706
00:42:08,026 --> 00:42:12,322
PEOPLE: [SINGING]
She stood there laughing

707
00:42:13,282 --> 00:42:15,075
-No, I kept missing 'em.
-JAMIE: Nah, you didn't.

708
00:42:15,158 --> 00:42:16,159
He's humble.

709
00:42:16,243 --> 00:42:17,244
-Our humble Spike.
-I felt the knife in my hand

710
00:42:17,327 --> 00:42:18,870
And she laughed no more

711
00:42:19,037 --> 00:42:20,455
The fuckin' giant killer!

712
00:42:20,539 --> 00:42:22,165
[CHEERING]

713
00:42:22,666 --> 00:42:27,379
My, my, my Delilah

714
00:42:29,923 --> 00:42:34,595
Why, why, why, Delilah?

715
00:42:34,761 --> 00:42:36,305
Go on. Go on, go.

716
00:42:37,264 --> 00:42:41,268
So before they come

717
00:42:41,435 --> 00:42:44,354
To break down the door

718
00:42:44,521 --> 00:42:49,902
Forgive me, Delilah
I just couldn't take any more

719
00:42:51,778 --> 00:42:53,488
Forgive me, Delilah

720
00:42:53,655 --> 00:42:57,576
I just couldn't take any more

721
00:42:57,743 --> 00:42:58,744
I gotta go.

722
00:42:58,827 --> 00:43:01,079
[PEOPLE VOCALISING END NOTE]

723
00:43:02,915 --> 00:43:04,917
[BOISTEROUS CHEERING
AND SHOUTING]

724
00:43:13,050 --> 00:43:14,218
[PANTING]

725
00:43:18,972 --> 00:43:20,182
JAMIE: In here.

726
00:43:24,519 --> 00:43:25,520
Go on, Rosey.

727
00:43:25,604 --> 00:43:26,605
[ROSEY GIGGLING]

728
00:43:26,688 --> 00:43:29,274
What... What are you...
What are you taking us here for?

729
00:43:29,358 --> 00:43:30,776
[BOTH PANTING]

730
00:43:30,859 --> 00:43:32,361
-BOTH: Oop.
-[ROSEY LAUGHS]

731
00:43:35,614 --> 00:43:36,615
JAMIE: Oh, Rosey.

732
00:43:36,698 --> 00:43:38,200
[BOTH PANTING]

733
00:43:38,283 --> 00:43:39,868
Oh, fuck. [MOANS]

734
00:43:42,537 --> 00:43:44,831
Oh, Rosey.

735
00:43:51,088 --> 00:43:52,673
[BOTH CONTINUE PANTING]

736
00:43:53,715 --> 00:43:55,217
[BOTH MOANING]

737
00:44:04,142 --> 00:44:05,435
[MUFFLED CREAK]

738
00:44:06,019 --> 00:44:07,145
[MUFFLED THUMP]

739
00:44:15,946 --> 00:44:17,030
[GROANS]

740
00:44:20,617 --> 00:44:21,785
Oh.

741
00:44:22,744 --> 00:44:23,829
Spike.

742
00:44:24,371 --> 00:44:26,707
I didn't expect to see you
until past midnight.

743
00:44:27,124 --> 00:44:28,542
Just came to see me mum.

744
00:44:28,709 --> 00:44:30,961
How was she? She all right?

745
00:44:31,837 --> 00:44:33,463
She's better than all right.

746
00:44:34,715 --> 00:44:36,091
We were up and about.

747
00:44:36,258 --> 00:44:37,676
We walked to the fields.

748
00:44:37,843 --> 00:44:40,554
She's got a lotta life in her
when she's not having a turn.

749
00:44:41,847 --> 00:44:44,266
But what about your day? Eh?

750
00:44:45,475 --> 00:44:46,727
More to the point.

751
00:44:47,019 --> 00:44:48,896
Dad's made it out
to be something it's not.

752
00:44:49,062 --> 00:44:50,063
Like what?

753
00:44:50,564 --> 00:44:51,565
Like I'm a hero.

754
00:44:51,982 --> 00:44:53,817
I expect you are, to him.

755
00:44:55,152 --> 00:44:56,862
Just feels like he's lying.

756
00:44:58,155 --> 00:45:00,282
So what did happen out there?

757
00:45:01,450 --> 00:45:03,785
-I shot one of the fat ones.
-Ah.

758
00:45:03,869 --> 00:45:05,871
-It was hardly moving.
-[LAUGHS]

759
00:45:05,954 --> 00:45:08,123
But then we got chased
by some of the fast ones,

760
00:45:09,041 --> 00:45:10,459
and I couldn't hit a thing.

761
00:45:12,377 --> 00:45:14,338
Then we just hid
until it got dark.

762
00:45:16,256 --> 00:45:17,716
I was just scared.

763
00:45:18,842 --> 00:45:19,968
Felt sick.

764
00:45:21,845 --> 00:45:23,597
I wanted to be home
with me mum.

765
00:45:23,889 --> 00:45:25,682
Your dad
probably felt the same.

766
00:45:29,311 --> 00:45:30,312
[SCOFFS]

767
00:45:30,395 --> 00:45:33,398
Tell you what, though,
never seen so much land.

768
00:45:33,482 --> 00:45:34,900
-Mmm.
-It was so big.

769
00:45:34,983 --> 00:45:36,318
What did you see?

770
00:45:36,401 --> 00:45:38,111
Well, hills...

771
00:45:38,695 --> 00:45:39,696
Forests...

772
00:45:41,698 --> 00:45:42,699
And a fire.

773
00:45:44,618 --> 00:45:46,036
A fire?

774
00:45:49,831 --> 00:45:51,667
I wonder if you saw
old Kelson.

775
00:45:52,125 --> 00:45:54,044
Didn't imagine
he was still alive.

776
00:45:56,880 --> 00:45:58,048
Was it southwest?

777
00:46:00,676 --> 00:46:03,011
Christ. That'll be Kelson.

778
00:46:03,845 --> 00:46:04,846
[EERIE SCREECH]

779
00:46:07,432 --> 00:46:08,433
Believe it or not,

780
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:10,769
he used to be my GP

781
00:46:11,979 --> 00:46:13,355
some 30 year back.

782
00:46:13,772 --> 00:46:15,857
-What's a GP?
-A doctor.

783
00:46:16,024 --> 00:46:17,818
-A doctor?
-Aye.

784
00:46:17,985 --> 00:46:20,737
Had his practice
just outside Whitley Bay.

785
00:46:23,699 --> 00:46:25,742
Dad said that he didn't know
what the fire was.

786
00:46:26,827 --> 00:46:28,870
And he says
all the real doctors are dead.

787
00:46:29,413 --> 00:46:31,415
That's why no one knows
what's wrong with Mum.

788
00:46:33,083 --> 00:46:35,127
Just feels like
he's lying about everything.

789
00:46:35,294 --> 00:46:37,337
Nah. You know what?

790
00:46:38,755 --> 00:46:39,840
[SAM SIGHS]

791
00:46:40,382 --> 00:46:42,092
He probably
didn't wanna spook you.

792
00:46:43,427 --> 00:46:44,636
Dr Kelson is...

793
00:46:47,222 --> 00:46:48,265
odd.

794
00:46:48,765 --> 00:46:49,808
How is he odd?

795
00:46:53,103 --> 00:46:54,605
What's so special
about the fire?

796
00:46:54,688 --> 00:46:56,106
If your dad
doesn't wanna talk about it,

797
00:46:56,189 --> 00:46:57,357
I don't think I should.

798
00:47:00,903 --> 00:47:03,363
Why don't you go back
to your party? Eh?

799
00:47:04,865 --> 00:47:06,199
I'm fine here wi' your mum.

800
00:47:06,283 --> 00:47:07,284
No.

801
00:47:07,910 --> 00:47:08,911
You go.

802
00:47:10,495 --> 00:47:11,747
I'll look after her now.

803
00:47:15,542 --> 00:47:16,543
Okay.

804
00:47:21,965 --> 00:47:23,133
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

805
00:47:23,217 --> 00:47:24,885
Got ya. [CHUCKLES]

806
00:47:50,410 --> 00:47:51,703
SPIKE: They're all lying, Mum.

807
00:47:55,999 --> 00:47:57,292
[ROOSTER CROWING]

808
00:48:01,046 --> 00:48:02,214
[ISLA BREATHING HEAVILY]

809
00:48:03,882 --> 00:48:05,759
Spike, will you go
to the shops for us?

810
00:48:07,094 --> 00:48:08,595
I need some Nurofen.

811
00:48:11,890 --> 00:48:12,849
Nurofen?

812
00:48:13,016 --> 00:48:14,768
It's me head. It's just...

813
00:48:17,145 --> 00:48:18,814
[PENSIVE EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

814
00:48:18,897 --> 00:48:19,898
[GROANS]

815
00:48:20,566 --> 00:48:22,276
Never mind. It doesn't matter.

816
00:48:22,359 --> 00:48:24,278
-[DOOR OPENS]
-JAMIE: Hello!

817
00:48:24,945 --> 00:48:26,405
ISLA: We're up here, love.

818
00:48:29,700 --> 00:48:31,827
Well, that was some party.

819
00:48:32,244 --> 00:48:34,079
Absolute carnage.

820
00:48:34,246 --> 00:48:35,372
-[GROANS]
-You look...

821
00:48:35,539 --> 00:48:36,582
You look like you've been

822
00:48:36,665 --> 00:48:38,166
dragged through
a hedge backwards.

823
00:48:38,834 --> 00:48:40,085
JAMIE: Maybe I did.

824
00:48:40,919 --> 00:48:43,130
I woke up in a wheat field.

825
00:48:43,297 --> 00:48:45,799
And where did you
disappear to, Spikey?

826
00:48:46,383 --> 00:48:49,511
Looked around and the guest
of honour had vanished.

827
00:48:50,596 --> 00:48:51,638
Just came home.

828
00:48:51,805 --> 00:48:53,682
Hey, giant-killer.

829
00:48:54,558 --> 00:48:56,059
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

830
00:48:57,352 --> 00:48:59,354
[PENSIVE EERIE
MUSIC CONTINUES]

831
00:49:12,701 --> 00:49:14,244
I'll make some breakfast.

832
00:49:27,257 --> 00:49:28,383
What's going on, Spike?

833
00:49:28,967 --> 00:49:30,594
Why didn't you tell us
there was a doctor

834
00:49:30,677 --> 00:49:31,678
that could see Mum?

835
00:49:32,054 --> 00:49:33,055
Doctor?

836
00:49:34,765 --> 00:49:35,807
We don't have a doctor.

837
00:49:35,891 --> 00:49:36,975
Haven't had a doctor here
in forever.

838
00:49:37,601 --> 00:49:39,228
Dr Kelson, Dad.

839
00:49:39,311 --> 00:49:41,230
The fire. On the mainland.

840
00:49:41,313 --> 00:49:42,606
Who've you been talking to?

841
00:49:43,857 --> 00:49:45,400
[SIGHS] So he is a doctor.

842
00:49:46,026 --> 00:49:47,069
Was it Sam?

843
00:49:47,653 --> 00:49:48,695
Bloody fool.

844
00:49:49,488 --> 00:49:50,906
Putting ideas in your head.

845
00:49:52,950 --> 00:49:55,035
He's not a doctor, Spike.

846
00:49:55,619 --> 00:49:58,080
Maybe he once was. Years ago.

847
00:49:59,039 --> 00:50:01,291
But he's long
since gone insane.

848
00:50:02,459 --> 00:50:03,502
What do you mean?

849
00:50:04,711 --> 00:50:06,421
Is he a doctor or not?

850
00:50:09,007 --> 00:50:10,467
Before you were born,

851
00:50:11,385 --> 00:50:12,594
we used to forage.

852
00:50:14,137 --> 00:50:15,222
But it got harder, you know,

853
00:50:15,305 --> 00:50:16,348
so you'd have
to travel further.

854
00:50:16,431 --> 00:50:18,809
And one day, it took a group
of us close to Kelson's.

855
00:50:20,227 --> 00:50:21,228
Right?

856
00:50:22,104 --> 00:50:24,064
Aye. 500 yards out,

857
00:50:24,940 --> 00:50:26,858
we started to smell death.

858
00:50:28,151 --> 00:50:29,987
Now understand, we were
well used to that smell.

859
00:50:30,070 --> 00:50:31,697
Back then,
the dead were everywhere.

860
00:50:32,739 --> 00:50:33,865
But this...

861
00:50:34,741 --> 00:50:36,118
this was totally different.

862
00:50:37,911 --> 00:50:39,288
This stench was like...

863
00:50:41,164 --> 00:50:42,374
it was like a wall.

864
00:50:42,791 --> 00:50:44,042
You could touch it.

865
00:50:46,336 --> 00:50:48,714
And we got
to the brow of this hill,

866
00:50:49,756 --> 00:50:51,008
and we looked down...

867
00:50:52,175 --> 00:50:53,302
[JAMIE SCOFFS]

868
00:50:54,094 --> 00:50:56,972
I've never seen
anything like it.

869
00:50:57,055 --> 00:50:59,057
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

870
00:50:59,683 --> 00:51:00,684
Corpses.

871
00:51:01,393 --> 00:51:02,603
Hundreds.

872
00:51:02,686 --> 00:51:04,229
[MUSIC SWELLS]

873
00:51:06,607 --> 00:51:09,276
Just arranged in lines.

874
00:51:10,944 --> 00:51:13,196
Men, women, children.

875
00:51:14,364 --> 00:51:16,283
And in the middle,
was this fire.

876
00:51:18,035 --> 00:51:19,870
Stood by it, was Kelson.

877
00:51:21,705 --> 00:51:24,625
For some unfathomable purpose,

878
00:51:24,708 --> 00:51:26,293
he'd dragged
all the bodies there.

879
00:51:27,461 --> 00:51:28,921
And a few seconds later,

880
00:51:29,004 --> 00:51:31,215
he turned around
and he looked right at us

881
00:51:31,423 --> 00:51:32,841
and he waved.

882
00:51:32,925 --> 00:51:35,594
Casually, like,
"Hey. Wanna come down, lads?"

883
00:51:38,972 --> 00:51:40,891
Yeah. We turned and ran.

884
00:51:41,642 --> 00:51:43,393
And in 15 years,

885
00:51:44,311 --> 00:51:45,979
none of us have been back.

886
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:49,566
Like I said.

887
00:51:51,068 --> 00:51:52,069
Insane.

888
00:51:52,152 --> 00:51:53,654
[SOFT CRACKLING]

889
00:51:55,864 --> 00:51:58,408
Oh, fuck. [SIGHS]

890
00:52:01,161 --> 00:52:02,537
Do you want Mum to die?

891
00:52:04,289 --> 00:52:05,791
'Course I don't.

892
00:52:07,709 --> 00:52:10,087
Ah, Spike,
what sort of question is that?

893
00:52:10,879 --> 00:52:12,256
What's really wrong with her?

894
00:52:13,131 --> 00:52:14,132
[SIGHS]

895
00:52:17,719 --> 00:52:18,720
I don't know.

896
00:52:20,097 --> 00:52:21,223
Is she dying?

897
00:52:24,643 --> 00:52:25,727
JAMIE: I don't know.

898
00:52:27,563 --> 00:52:29,022
I think she's dying.

899
00:52:30,065 --> 00:52:31,358
And so do you.

900
00:52:33,402 --> 00:52:34,486
If she dies,

901
00:52:34,945 --> 00:52:36,572
are you gonna be with Rosey?

902
00:52:38,156 --> 00:52:39,533
Watch your mouth.

903
00:52:39,616 --> 00:52:41,159
What would her Davey
think about that?

904
00:52:41,243 --> 00:52:43,078
I said,
watch your bloody mouth!

905
00:52:44,037 --> 00:52:45,414
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

906
00:52:46,123 --> 00:52:47,124
Son...

907
00:52:47,541 --> 00:52:48,876
ISLA: Jamie!

908
00:52:50,294 --> 00:52:51,295
Spike!

909
00:52:51,920 --> 00:52:53,213
[DOOR CLOSES]

910
00:52:54,172 --> 00:52:55,215
[ISLA MOANS]

911
00:52:56,675 --> 00:52:59,511
Oh, it's pounding, Spike.
Pounding.

912
00:52:59,970 --> 00:53:01,388
I know, Mum. I'm sorry.

913
00:53:03,307 --> 00:53:04,474
[SPIKE SNIFFLING]

914
00:53:06,476 --> 00:53:08,604
Need some water, love?
I'll go get you some.

915
00:53:10,272 --> 00:53:12,274
Get the fuck away from us.

916
00:53:13,191 --> 00:53:14,234
"From us"?

917
00:53:17,112 --> 00:53:18,238
[PANTING]

918
00:53:19,489 --> 00:53:20,616
You heard us.

919
00:53:40,219 --> 00:53:41,511
Just go away, Dad.

920
00:53:52,105 --> 00:53:53,106
[DOOR SLAMS]

921
00:53:53,190 --> 00:53:55,609
[PANTING]

922
00:53:57,319 --> 00:53:59,613
-[WIND WHISTLING]
-[SEAGULLS CALLING]

923
00:54:21,301 --> 00:54:22,469
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

924
00:54:26,014 --> 00:54:27,015
SPIKE: There's a fire!

925
00:54:28,725 --> 00:54:29,935
There's a... Run!

926
00:54:30,018 --> 00:54:32,104
ANTHONY: Fuckin' smoke, look.
SPIKE: Ant, Mark!

927
00:54:32,187 --> 00:54:33,814
-There's a fire!
-Go, go, go on! Go on!

928
00:54:33,897 --> 00:54:35,190
SPIKE: There's fire
in the main barn!

929
00:54:35,274 --> 00:54:36,358
You've got to go!

930
00:54:36,441 --> 00:54:37,901
I can't leave the gate, Spike.

931
00:54:39,653 --> 00:54:40,696
SPIKE: You have to.

932
00:54:40,779 --> 00:54:42,531
That's why they sent me.

933
00:54:42,614 --> 00:54:45,075
I'll be on the siren.
But you've gotta go now.

934
00:54:45,450 --> 00:54:47,077
They need every man,
they said!

935
00:54:47,369 --> 00:54:48,912
-Go!
-For fuck's sake.

936
00:54:48,996 --> 00:54:51,081
SPIKE: Hurry. Go.
ANTHONY: Fuckin'...

937
00:54:51,164 --> 00:54:52,708
Keep your eyes on the horizon.

938
00:54:52,791 --> 00:54:54,459
And stay on that siren!

939
00:54:55,294 --> 00:54:56,670
MAN: Gonna get more water!

940
00:54:56,837 --> 00:54:58,422
WOMAN: Fetch more water!

941
00:55:01,800 --> 00:55:03,010
MAN: Fire!

942
00:55:04,928 --> 00:55:07,055
WOMAN: Get more water. Go!

943
00:55:07,139 --> 00:55:08,140
MAN: Fire!

944
00:55:08,223 --> 00:55:09,558
[CLAMOURING]

945
00:55:10,809 --> 00:55:12,102
[SPIKE PANTING]

946
00:55:12,978 --> 00:55:15,063
Come on, Mum. Let's go.

947
00:55:15,772 --> 00:55:16,940
MAN 1: Get water! Water!

948
00:55:17,024 --> 00:55:18,400
MAN 2: Get some more water
from the sea!

949
00:55:18,734 --> 00:55:19,776
ISLA: Where are we going?

950
00:55:20,277 --> 00:55:21,445
The beach.

951
00:55:21,612 --> 00:55:22,988
And the fields.

952
00:55:23,405 --> 00:55:24,573
-We're going to the beach?
-Yeah.

953
00:55:35,500 --> 00:55:37,085
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

954
00:55:57,022 --> 00:55:58,482
ISLA: This is the mainland.

955
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:01,401
SPIKE: Yeah.

956
00:56:01,944 --> 00:56:02,945
ISLA: But we can't...

957
00:56:04,154 --> 00:56:05,656
We can't be on the mainland.

958
00:56:06,657 --> 00:56:08,033
It's too dangerous. It's...

959
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:09,785
-It's okay, Mum.
-No.

960
00:56:09,868 --> 00:56:12,037
-I know how to keep us safe.
-No, no, no, this isn't right.

961
00:56:12,120 --> 00:56:14,414
It's not right. Where's...?
[PANTING]

962
00:56:14,498 --> 00:56:15,707
Jamie?

963
00:56:16,542 --> 00:56:17,543
Where's...

964
00:56:19,503 --> 00:56:20,629
Where's Dad?

965
00:56:21,046 --> 00:56:22,381
-Dad's not here.
-Then we...

966
00:56:23,298 --> 00:56:25,050
Then we have to go back now.
Back home.

967
00:56:25,133 --> 00:56:26,134
We have to run, or we...

968
00:56:26,218 --> 00:56:27,219
Mum...

969
00:56:28,095 --> 00:56:30,639
We can't go back. Tide's in.

970
00:56:30,722 --> 00:56:32,891
Oh, God.

971
00:56:34,851 --> 00:56:35,936
Going to see a doctor.

972
00:56:36,019 --> 00:56:37,354
What? A doctor?

973
00:56:37,437 --> 00:56:38,730
-A real doctor.
-No.

974
00:56:38,814 --> 00:56:39,982
From the old days.

975
00:56:40,649 --> 00:56:42,150
Something wrong with you, Mum.

976
00:56:45,362 --> 00:56:46,863
The doctor's
gonna make you better.

977
00:56:50,659 --> 00:56:51,660
Okay?

978
00:56:53,203 --> 00:56:54,204
Okay.

979
00:56:54,288 --> 00:56:56,290
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

980
00:57:23,901 --> 00:57:25,068
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

981
00:57:35,454 --> 00:57:37,122
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

982
00:57:37,205 --> 00:57:38,874
[PANTING TIREDLY]

983
00:57:45,797 --> 00:57:46,798
Okay, Mum.

984
00:57:47,716 --> 00:57:49,259
We'll stop here for the night.

985
00:57:51,678 --> 00:57:52,846
We'll stay there.

986
00:57:52,930 --> 00:57:54,890
-[WIND BLOWING]
-[BIRDS CHIRPING]

987
00:58:00,062 --> 00:58:02,689
[RAIN PATTERING ECHOES]

988
00:58:08,362 --> 00:58:10,530
[ISLA CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

989
00:58:12,241 --> 00:58:13,367
Is your dad silly?

990
00:58:19,122 --> 00:58:20,249
-Dad?
-Yeah.

991
00:58:20,791 --> 00:58:22,584
Silly with ya. Jokey.

992
00:58:26,213 --> 00:58:27,673
Your granddad was so silly.

993
00:58:29,216 --> 00:58:30,551
You wouldn't believe how much.

994
00:58:33,262 --> 00:58:35,472
Everyone else thought
he was so serious...

995
00:58:36,390 --> 00:58:38,225
but around me, he was daft.

996
00:58:41,019 --> 00:58:42,271
Is your dad like that...

997
00:58:43,772 --> 00:58:45,274
you know, when it's just
the two of you?

998
00:58:47,359 --> 00:58:48,443
No.

999
00:58:51,446 --> 00:58:53,323
ISLA: Just wanting to make sure
you're tough enough.

1000
00:58:54,575 --> 00:58:55,576
Like him.

1001
00:59:00,205 --> 00:59:01,790
You know,
when I look in your face...

1002
00:59:03,709 --> 00:59:05,419
I see your granddad's eyes.

1003
00:59:06,295 --> 00:59:07,337
It's nice.

1004
00:59:11,383 --> 00:59:12,426
[BOTH LAUGH]

1005
00:59:12,718 --> 00:59:13,719
Exactly.

1006
00:59:18,265 --> 00:59:19,641
[GRUNTS]

1007
00:59:26,732 --> 00:59:27,983
You should get some sleep.

1008
00:59:30,027 --> 00:59:32,321
I'm gonna stay awake.
Keep watch.

1009
00:59:32,863 --> 00:59:33,864
Okay, Dad.

1010
00:59:44,583 --> 00:59:46,210
[RAIN PATTERING CONTINUING]

1011
00:59:55,010 --> 00:59:56,511
[CROWS CAWING]

1012
01:00:14,738 --> 01:00:17,032
[CAWING]

1013
01:00:19,618 --> 01:00:21,495
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1014
01:00:33,966 --> 01:00:35,634
[CAWING]

1015
01:00:48,897 --> 01:00:50,357
[SOFT GROWLING]

1016
01:01:28,103 --> 01:01:29,146
[MUSIC SWELLS]

1017
01:01:42,409 --> 01:01:43,452
[SPITS]

1018
01:01:46,496 --> 01:01:47,581
[GROWLS]

1019
01:01:49,124 --> 01:01:50,876
[GROWLING HOARSELY]

1020
01:01:58,508 --> 01:02:01,345
[GASPING]

1021
01:02:03,722 --> 01:02:04,723
What?

1022
01:02:07,976 --> 01:02:09,102
What happened?

1023
01:02:10,604 --> 01:02:11,605
I don't know.

1024
01:02:13,941 --> 01:02:14,942
SPIKE: Here.

1025
01:02:17,903 --> 01:02:19,071
Gotta go.

1026
01:02:22,199 --> 01:02:23,742
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

1027
01:02:24,493 --> 01:02:26,662
-[GRUNTS]
-[THUDDING]

1028
01:02:40,133 --> 01:02:42,135
[ANIMALS CHITTER]

1029
01:02:48,016 --> 01:02:49,768
[GROWLING ECHOES]

1030
01:02:50,519 --> 01:02:53,355
-[SCREECHING IN DISTANCE]
-[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN SWEDISH]

1031
01:02:56,441 --> 01:02:57,776
-[BONES CRACK]
-[SOLDIER SCREAMS]

1032
01:02:59,152 --> 01:03:00,779
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN SWEDISH]

1033
01:03:00,862 --> 01:03:02,906
[SCREECHING APPROACHING]

1034
01:03:04,408 --> 01:03:06,159
[INFECTED SCREECHING]

1035
01:03:12,457 --> 01:03:14,918
[SOLDIERS SHOUT IN SWEDISH]

1036
01:03:20,299 --> 01:03:22,509
[SCREECHING, GROWLING]

1037
01:03:29,141 --> 01:03:30,309
-[PANTING]
-[SCREECHING]

1038
01:03:31,476 --> 01:03:32,895
[GROWLING]

1039
01:03:37,858 --> 01:03:40,152
[VOMITING]

1040
01:03:42,988 --> 01:03:44,615
[GROWLING]

1041
01:03:47,910 --> 01:03:49,536
[SCREECHING, GROWLING]

1042
01:03:56,543 --> 01:03:58,295
[SOLDIERS SHOUT IN SWEDISH]

1043
01:04:03,342 --> 01:04:07,012
[SOLDIERS PANTING]

1044
01:04:08,764 --> 01:04:10,515
[SCREECHING]

1045
01:04:15,812 --> 01:04:17,356
[PANTING]

1046
01:04:18,190 --> 01:04:19,650
[SPEAKING SWEDISH] Ugly fuckers.

1047
01:04:21,860 --> 01:04:23,070
Okay, move back.

1048
01:04:23,987 --> 01:04:26,198
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1049
01:04:45,217 --> 01:04:46,718
[SOLDIERS BREATHING HEAVILY]

1050
01:05:13,245 --> 01:05:15,122
-[SCREECHING IN DISTANCE]
-[SOLDIERS GASP]

1051
01:05:18,458 --> 01:05:20,711
-[ROARING]
-[SCREAMS]

1052
01:05:20,794 --> 01:05:22,713
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1053
01:05:22,796 --> 01:05:24,715
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN SWEDISH]

1054
01:05:27,759 --> 01:05:31,471
[ROARING]

1055
01:05:45,444 --> 01:05:47,446
[MUSIC FADES]

1056
01:05:51,950 --> 01:05:53,327
[SCREAMS]

